
Piedmont
instance
Piedmont (/ˈpiːdmɒnt/ PEED-mont; Italian: Piemonte, [pjeˈmonte]; Piedmontese and Occitan: Piemont; French: Piémont) is one of the 20 regions of Italy. It has an area of 25,402 square kilometres (9,808 sq mi) and a population of about 4.6 million. The capital of Piedmont is Turin.
